(Sorry for using screenshot, The OCR I tried screw up the formating of the gdb log)

Hi, I was working on a Project that unfortunately I am not allowed to share the code with. 
I notice that the verilating time for this project is abnormally long, Actually, it dont finish at all. (> 3Hr)

Out project involve a 16x16 CGRA array, a total 256 CGRA units.  Each CGRA unit contains some simple floating units and some muxes. I will not call our design "huge", just a "fine" size, and the memory utilization is <20%, so I was very confused on why it is so slow.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------- Research ----------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
So I started to digging in to the source code of verilator. 
I noticed that in the **ScopeAll** function inside **V3Scope.cpp** is where the verilator stuck on our project.

What I did next is profiling the ScopeAll function.
I noticed that the time spend on each instance of CGRA unit, in ScopeAll's **_visit_** functions, grows in a abnormal way as shown below(Ignore all the Y00 case as they have different CGRA unit instance):
```
V3Const.cpp:3980:  constIlYAll:
V3Scope.cpp:428:    scopeAll:
